cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on UAV-assisted cellular communication and proposes a new approach for offloading terrestrial base stations. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of a high capacity link for connecting the tethered UAV to the core network, which involves information transmission and processing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for cellular traffic offloading and analyzes its performance using stochastic geometry-based analysis. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of UAVs for cellular communication, which can involve multimedia data transmission. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of UAVs for cellular communication can raise security concerns, which may be discussed in the paper.
